answers.body_markdown:
You have a logical flaw in your `fix_classes_with_corresponding_projects` function: `indexes_to_fix` contains the index **values** (not the index positions) of the rows to fix. You then select with `iloc`, which selects rows by position. What you need is

    # Update the records
    df.loc[indexes_to_fix, &#39;Teaching Type&#39;] = &quot;Practical Work&quot;

instead of

    df.iloc[indexes_to_fix, df.columns.get_loc(&#39;Teaching Type&#39;)] = &quot;Practical Work&quot;

So your original code worked only by coincidence. If you had a non-numeric index (e.g. creating the sample dataframe with `index=list(&#39;abcdefghi&#39;)`), the flaw would have become immediatetly apparent.

