answers.body_markdown:
in your code by calling `filteredMailList = mailList;` you are actually removing your original filteredMailList List (you don&#39;t have any refrence to that list anymore) and changing it to the mailList. so both filteredMailList and mailList points to a single List in memory

you can create a clone list from mailList like :

```dart
filteredMailList = [...mailList]; // or filteredMailList = mailList.toList();
```

or keep your original refrence and copy all items from mailList

```dart
filteredMailList.clear();
filteredMailList.addAll(mailList);
```

